interface.name: NodeSetData
interface.javadoc: An abstract representation of a Data type containing a node-set. The type (class) and ordering of the nodes contained in the set are not defined by this class; instead that behavior should be defined by NodeSetData subclasses. Sean Mullan JSR 105 Expert Group 1.6

Returns a read-only iterator over the nodes contained in this NodeSetData in document order. Attempts to modify the returned iterator via the remove method throw UnsupportedOperationException. an Iterator over the nodes in this NodeSetData in document order
